<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY REMOVAL (IF EQUIPPED)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY REMOVAL (IF EQUIPPED)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>FLYWHEEL REMOVAL</title>
            <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                        TO SUPPORT THE BACK END OF THE ENGINE WHEN SERVICING THE REAR PTO ASSEMBLY.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The rear oil seal can be serviced in chassis. The procedure is performed as part of the engine
                        overhaul or separately, when required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>THE REAR OIL SEAL IS IN THE REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY. this rear seal is different than the
                        engine rear oil seal.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two (2) flywheel mounting bolts located at the 3 and 9 o'clock positions. Install
                    two (2) guide dowel pins, made locally, at these locations (F
                    <emph type="bold">igure</emph>
                    <hotlnk document="e160_179.xml" xrefid="ef1600732">7.32</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove remaining ten (10) flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide flywheel out of the flywheel housing and off guide dowel pins.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>after the flywheel has been removed, do not to remove the guide dowel pins from the
                            crankshaft flange (
                            <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                                <hotlnk document="e160_179.xml" xrefid="ef1600733">7.33</hotlnk>
                            </emph>
                            ).
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>FOR APPLICATIONS USING AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSIONS, TAKE NOTE OF POSITION AND ORIENTATION OF
                            FLEXPLATE(S), SPACERS AND REINFORCING RING.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
